-709361093.text: "Here, we show that roscovitine, a cyclin dependent kinase (CDK) inhibitor that inhibits CDK-1, CDK-2, CDK-5, CDK-7, and CDK-9 due to competitive binding to the ATP site on the kinases, causes significant DNA damage followed by p53 dependent cell death in human papilloma virus (HPV)-positive, but not in HPV negative, head and neck cancer cells."
